<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName authority="Cardoso, Bastos-Pereira, Souza &amp; Ferreira, 2021" authorityName="Cardoso 1 &amp; Bastos-Pereira 1 &amp; Souza 2 &amp; Ferreira 1" authorityYear="2021" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae" genus="Chaimowiczia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chaimowiczia uai" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Chaimowiczia uai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is characterized by the concave shape of pereonites epimera, with pereonite 1 epimeron directed frontward; round antennal lobes; pleonites 3-5 epimera with tips well developed, pleonite 5 surpassing apex of telson; and uropods endopod longer than exopod.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Maximum length: male, 8 mm. Colorless, eyes absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A cephalon, dorsal view B cephalon, frontal view C epimeron 1, dorsal view D pereopod 1 merus, propodus, carpus and dactylus E pereopod 2 merus F Uropod. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 100 µm (B); 400 µm (C); 500 µm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552957" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7A, B</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface smooth covered with scale setae with long base (reaching half the total length) and free sensory hair (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A cephalon, dorsal view B cephalon, frontal view C epimeron 1, dorsal view D pereopod 1 merus, propodus, carpus and dactylus E pereopod 2 merus F Uropod. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 100 µm (B); 400 µm (C); 500 µm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552957" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7C</figureCitation>
). Cephalon (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A cephalon, dorsal view B cephalon, frontal view C epimeron 1, dorsal view D pereopod 1 merus, propodus, carpus and dactylus E pereopod 2 merus F Uropod. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 100 µm (B); 400 µm (C); 500 µm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552957" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7A, B</figureCitation>
) vertex with lateral grooves; frons with distinct suprantennal line, downward in middle; round antennal lobes. Body convex; pereonite 1 postero-lateral corners well developed and projected forward, lateral margin concave; pereonite 7 slightly surpassing distal margin of pleonite 2; pleon 3-5 epimera well developed, pleonite 5 surpassing telson apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6A</figureCitation>
). Telson (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6B</figureCitation>
) with distal half subtriangular depressed, rounded apex. Antennula (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6C</figureCitation>
) with three articles covered with setae, distal article as long as second article, with two apical aesthetascs. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6D</figureCitation>
) surpasses pereonite 1 when extended backwards, fifth article of peduncle shorter than flagellum; flagellum with three articles. Left mandible with two penicils (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6E</figureCitation>
); right mandible with one penicil (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6F</figureCitation>
). Maxillula (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6G</figureCitation>
) outer ramus with 5 + 5 teeth, apically entire, and two thick plumose stalks; inner ramus with three penicils, two of them stout. Maxilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6H</figureCitation>
) with bilobate apex, inner lobe wider than outer lobe with several setae on distal margin. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6I</figureCitation>
) basis distal portion slightly wider than basal; palp apex with tufts of setae; endite rectangular, shorter than palp, setose, apex with one rounded penicil between two strong teeth, inner tooth longer. Pereopod 1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A pereopod 1 B pereopod 7 C genital papilla and pleopod 1 D pleopod 2 E pleopod 3 exopod F pleopod 4 exopod G pleopod 5 exopod. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552958" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">8C</figureCitation>
) antennal grooming brush composed by pectinate scales longitudinally on frontal face of propodus and carpus, dactylus with one claw; pereopod 7 basis with water conducting system scale rows. Uropod (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A habitus, dorsal view B pleonite 5, telson and uropod, dorsal view C antennula D antenna E right mandible F left mandible G maxillula H maxilla I maxilliped. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B, D-J); 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552956" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">6B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Chaimowiczia uai sp. nov. Male A cephalon, dorsal view B cephalon, frontal view C epimeron 1, dorsal view D pereopod 1 merus, propodus, carpus and dactylus E pereopod 2 merus F Uropod. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 100 µm (B); 400 µm (C); 500 µm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.39.65305.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/552957" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7F</figureCitation>
) protopod surpasses distal margin of telson, covered with pectinate scales; endopod longer than exopod, inserted at the same level.
</paragraph>
